  \li{RMSProp}
  \li{Adam}
}
\p{A key formula to remember:
##{\text{total memory} \approx 4 \times (\text{params} + \text{activations} + \text{grad size} + \text{optimizer state size})}
}
}
\remark{
Another useful trick is to use [low precision](DEQV) for forward pass activations, then use \code{float32} for gradients and network parameters.
}
